abstract.text: Record or play audio, convert formats, parse audio streams, and configure your audio session.
Specifies the current level metering information for one channel of an audio queue.
Identifiers for audio queue properties.
Begins playing or recording audio.
Stops playing or recording audio.
Value is a read-only
value representing the number of channels in the audio hardware device associated with an audio queue.
Value is a read-only
value representing the sampling rate of the audio hardware device associated with an audio queue.
Describes an audio queue channel layout.
Value is a  read-only
value that indicates the most recent error (if any) encountered by the audio queue’s internal encoding/decoding process.
The unique identifier (UID) of the audio hardware device.
A read-only array of level meter status structures.
Value is a read-only array of
structures, one array element per audio channel. The member values in the structure are in decibels.
Value is a read/write

value that is the size of the buffer into which a playback (output) audio queue decodes buffers. A larger buffer provides more reliability and  better long-term performance at the expense of memory and decreased responsiveness in some situations.
Value is a read/write
value that indicates whether audio level metering is enabled for an audio queue.
= metering off,
= metering on.
Value is a read-only
value indicating whether or not the audio queue is running. A nonzero value means running;
means stopped. A notification is sent when the associated audio queue starts or stops, which may occur sometime after the
or
function is called.

Value is a read/write void pointer to a block of memory, which you set up, containing an audio format magic cookie. If the audio format you are playing or recording to requires a magic cookie, you must set a value for this property before enqueuing any buffers.
Value is a read-only
value that is the size, in bytes, of the largest single packet of data in the output format. Primarily useful when encoding VBR compressed data.
An audio queue’s data format.
